WEBVTT

00:01.434 --> 00:03.295
As long you are still married
we cannot be together.

00:03.296 --> 00:04.969
I need to think of my daughters.

00:04.970 --> 00:07.598
I moved my family to Berlin for you.

00:07.599 --> 00:09.319
You came to join the academy.

00:09.320 --> 00:10.837
I do wish Elsa could have joined us.

00:10.838 --> 00:12.538
Woman: Apparently she's
gone away to Esson.

00:12.539 --> 00:14.707
Mileva: That's where Albert is.

00:14.708 --> 00:16.976
When were you going
to tell me about Elsa?

00:16.977 --> 00:18.111
Albert: I want a divorce.

00:18.112 --> 00:20.183
Mileva: I am not letting
you walk away from the boys.

00:20.184 --> 00:21.217
Einstein: Fritz Haber.

00:21.218 --> 00:23.453
The man that pulled
nitrogen out of thin air.

00:23.454 --> 00:24.821
Fritz: I'm a proud war veteran.

00:24.822 --> 00:25.922
Einstein: Really, Fritz?

00:25.923 --> 00:27.991
You're proud of your
military service?

00:27.992 --> 00:29.659
[Speaking foreign language].

00:29.660 --> 00:31.795
Albert: The only way to
confirm general relativity

00:31.796 --> 00:33.963
is during a solar eclipse.

00:33.964 --> 00:36.132
Fritz: The kaiser has
declared war on Russia.

00:36.133 --> 00:39.903
Mileva: Your foundation for
general relativity is flawed.

00:39.904 --> 00:41.438
Albert: I could
have been ruined.

00:41.439 --> 00:43.281
- You wanted me to fail.
- Mileva: You're right.

00:43.282 --> 00:45.001
Albert: Mileva has
agreed to end things.

00:45.002 --> 00:46.477
Elsa: There is quite
a difference between

00:46.478 --> 00:48.191
separation and divorce.

00:48.192 --> 00:50.560
Albert: Mileva I wanted to end
our marriage, I didn't want

00:50.561 --> 00:52.128
to lose my whole family.

00:52.129 --> 00:55.031
Mileva: You can't have
everything, Albert.

01:01.038 --> 01:09.138
♪

